			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The nice(?) thing about something with constant unchanging IRQ requirements is that you could use one or two ICs as your external IRQ generator, making it easy to add this functionality to any almost any hardware.<br /><br />A lot of pirate games used a (74')4040 to generate an IRQ every 2ⁿ cycles. Since your interval here is 160cy, you only need to add an AND gate (to set that period; = NOT(NAND)) and a NAND gate to drive the /IRQ pin on the card edge.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
